### Recovery & Troubleshooting
| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `/sdd doctor` | Validate SDD setup (python3, jq, config, state, lock, hooks) |
| `/sdd reset` | Reset SDD state (default: operational state only) |
| `/sdd reset --full` | Remove ALL generated artifacts (state + docs + branches) |
| `/sdd reset --dry-run` | Preview what would be deleted without doing it |
| `/sdd unlock` | Remove stale orchestrator lock |
| `/sdd rollback` | Revert last `[SDD]` auto-commit |

When invoked as `/sdd reset`, run the script with the appropriate flags:
- `/sdd reset` → `bash .claude/scripts/sdd-reset.sh`
- `/sdd reset --full` → `bash .claude/scripts/sdd-reset.sh --full`
- `/sdd reset --dry-run` → `bash .claude/scripts/sdd-reset.sh --dry-run`
- `/sdd reset --full --dry-run` → `bash .claude/scripts/sdd-reset.sh --full --dry-run`

**Command ownership note**:
- Skill-routed commands are those with explicit Agent Mode mappings above.
- `/sdd doctor`, `/sdd reset`, `/sdd unlock`, and `/sdd rollback` are CLI utility commands, not skill-routed agent modes.

## Gap Severity Classification

Two complementary systems used across all agents:

**Descriptive** (used by Completeness Reviewer and Challenger):

| Severity | Maps To | Action |
|----------|---------|--------|
| CRITICAL | `escalate` | Block pipeline, human required |
| IMPORTANT | `retry` | Re-spawn agent (max 3 retries) |
| WARNING | `retry` | Re-spawn agent (max 3 retries) |
| MINOR | `skip` | Log and continue |

**Action-based** (used by Orchestrator):
- `escalate`: security breach, data loss, fundamental flaw, system-wide impact
- `retry`: missing error handling, API contract gaps, edge cases, runtime failures
- `skip`: cosmetic, formatting, documentation, readability

**When uncertain, default to `retry`.**

## Context Loading

At session start, load:
- `AGENTS.md` (if exists — L0 context for all pipeline agents)
- `docs/sdd/phase-index.md` (if exists)
- `docs/sdd/context-digest.md` (if exists)
- `docs/sdd/{epic}/{task}/digests/{previous_phase}-digest.md` (if exists — L0 compact summary from upstream phase)
- Current skill `SKILL.md` and required guidelines
- Phase-required artifacts only (see `.claude/skills/shared/context-management.md`)
- Agent learnings — CRITICAL/WARNING first, sorted by trust level (from `.claude/skills/sdd-{agent}/learnings/`)

**Context budget**: 660 lines / 27KB per agent maximum (configured limit). L0 (always) -> L1 (phase-required) -> L2 (on-demand only).

Do NOT bulk-load `docs/` by default. Load `docs/best-practices.md`, `docs/tech-stack.md`, `docs/project/project-init.yaml`, or `docs/project/project-goal.md` only when the active phase requires them.

## Workflows

**Full SDD Cycle** (for new features):
```
Init -> Best Practices -> Goal -> Project Manager -> Challenger -> Designer -> Unit Test-Writer -> Integration Test-Writer -> Implementer -> Reviewer
```

**TDD Cycle** (when design exists):
```
Unit Test-Writer -> Integration Test-Writer -> Implementer -> Reviewer
```

**Automated Task Pipeline** (via `/sdd task <id>` — `sdd-task-orchestrator`, 19 phases):
```
Designer -> Validation Loop -> Challenger (tech+security) ->
Security Review (design) ->
★HUMAN CHECKPOINT: Design+Security (Pre-Reveal → Reveal → Decide; risk-routed) ->
Unit Tests -> Validation Loop ->
Integration Tests -> Validation Loop ->
★HUMAN CHECKPOINT: Tests (Pre-Reveal → Reveal → Decide; risk-routed) ->
Implementer -> Coverage Check -> SAST Gate -> Mutation Test -> Validation Loop ->
Security Review (impl) + Aikido ->
★HUMAN CHECKPOINT: Impl+Security (Pre-Reveal → Reveal → Decide; risk-routed) ->
Code Reviewer -> Feedback Collector
```

**Project Setup Pipeline** (via `/sdd setup-project` — `sdd-project-setup`, 18 steps):
```
Prerequisite Validation -> Project Init -> Setup Report -> Codebase Analysis ->
Best Practices -> Project Goal -> Epics -> Tasks -> Populate epics[] -> Task Tracking Sync
```

**Automated Bug Pipeline** (via `/sdd bug` or `/sdd fix` — `sdd-bug-orchestrator`):
```
Init -> [Tracking: In Progress] ->
Bug Analyst -> Validation Loop -> ★HUMAN CHECKPOINT (Pre-Reveal → Reveal → Decide; always full protocol) ->
Bug Test-Writer -> Validation Loop ->
Bug Implementer -> Validation Loop -> [Security Review (if auth/authz/validation touched)] ->
★HUMAN CHECKPOINT (Pre-Reveal → Reveal → Decide; always full protocol) ->
Bug Reviewer -> Feedback Collector -> Git PR -> [Tracking: In Review]
```
Bug pipeline checkpoints always use full Pre-Reveal protocol regardless of task risk classification (bugs are inherently high-consequence).

**Bug -> Feature Escalation**: If Bug Analyst or Bug Implementer flags that the fix requires architectural changes (new APIs, schema changes, >5 files), the pipeline pauses and asks the user to switch to the feature pipeline. If confirmed, state transitions to `goal.type: "feature"`, `phase: "design"`, and `bug-analysis.md` is passed as context to the Designer.

**Turbo Mode** (`/sdd task <id> --turbo` or `/sdd turbo`):
- **Risk-aware routing** (unless `risk.turbo_override: true` reverts to v1.0 behavior):
  - **HOTL**: All non-security checkpoints auto-approved; async notification only. Implementation checkpoint blocks if security findings >= HIGH
  - **HIC**: Design+tests checkpoints auto-approved; implementation checkpoint requires human review (Pre-Reveal → Reveal → Decide)
  - **HITL**: Turbo disabled entirely — all checkpoints block for human review
- **Security exception**: Checkpoints with security findings are NEVER auto-approved regardless of risk level
- Only `escalate` gaps surface; `skip`/`retry` auto-approved
- Challenger phase skipped
- Circuit breaker: 3 consecutive tasks with `retry` gaps -> auto-downgrade to normal mode

**Legacy Orchestrator Pipeline** (via `/sdd orchestrate` — deprecated, use `/sdd task` or `/sdd turbo all`):
```
Init -> [Setup] -> Best Practices -> [Challenge BP] -> Goal -> [Challenge Goal] -> PM (Epic Mode) -> Validation Loop -> Challenge ->
  For each epic -> PM (Task Mode) -> Validation Loop -> Challenge ->
    For each task: (see Automated Task Pipeline above)
```

**Important**: Stop after each phase. Do NOT auto-chain (unless in orchestrator mode).

